
[1]applaud

   APPLAUD', v.t. [L. applaudo; ad and plaudo, to make a noise by clapping
   the hands; Eng. loud.]

   1. To praise by clapping the hands, acclamation, or other significant
   sign.

   2. To praise by words, actions or other means; to express approbation
   of; to commend; used in a general sense.
